article.headline: St. Francis, NY 60, Hofstra 57
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Robert Hines scored 21 points and hit a lay-up with 38 seconds to play to break a tie, and the Terriers held on for a 60-57 win over Hofstra on Wednesday night. Lateef Willis connected on two free throws to put the Terriers (2-2) up 52-46 with 3:12 remaining. Hofstra (1-2) came back and tied it at 57 on a jumper by Arminas Urbutis with 55 seconds to go. After Hines' lay-up gave St. Francis a 59-57 lead, Antoine Agudio missed a jumper with 18 seconds to play for Hofstra. Hines got the rebound for the Terriers, and after he was fouled he made 1-of-2 free throws to complete the scoring. Agudio's 3-pointer with 2 seconds remaining went off the rim. Dane Johnson scored 17 points for Hofstra. Charles Jenkins added 11.
